race.comment: The penny has dropped for GARINION RIGH (10) who has put back-to-back wins together and is racing with a lot of confidence of late. Gets in well at the weights with the claim and should get a cosy run in transit from gate two. Plenty to like about her prospects. KEEP ON RUNNING (3) is a four-time winner here on his home circuit and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside marble. Sure to run well again. KICKAGOAL KENNY (5) is a consistent conveyance who has hit the top-five at his past eight outings. Can play a role in the outcome. CANDLELIT (4) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and looks one for the exotics players.
